mohammad helaluddin, general secretary of the bangladesh youth union, told reporters the march was to call attention to government injustice and the suffering of the unemployed and their families. the union sponsored the protest
helaluddin called on the government to end a hiring freeze imposed 2{ years ago. the ban was issued because of financial contraints
bangladesh, with a population of 105 million, is one of the poorest nations in the world, with a per capita annual income of $160
the marchers took about nine hours to walk from the national mausoleum at savar northwest of the capital to a monument in downtown dhaka
